JOHANNESBURG - South African construction company Murray and Roberts has been acquired by a German counterpart.Engineering and construction group ATM has bought a 25-percent stake in the group, making it the largest shareholder.Several investors have already disposed of their shares in the local company.Coronation Fund Managers let go of its 15 percent interest last week.It has since been followed by major shareholders Allan Gray and Sanlam Investment Management.The firm s stock jumped to an almost 6-month-high, with the company saying it wasn't aware of the reasons behind the rise.eNCA